string.name: confirm_reset_factory_with_esim_content
string.value:
This will permanently delete system data, installed apps and their data, personal files (like music and images), as well as eSIMs.

You can choose to keep eSIMs on your device if you don't want to delete them. Deleting an eSIM removes all associated data from your device, but does not cancel your mobile plan.

Before resetting your device, make sure that you back up any important data. Please don't store backups on the device's internal storage, as this will be wiped when the device is reset.
